---
import EditorLayout from '../layouts/EditorLayout.astro';
import LineGutter from '../components/nvim/LineGutter.astro';
---

<EditorLayout title="About" description="About Dian Hanifudin Subhi">
  <LineGutter>
    <article class="prose">
      <h1>About</h1>

      <p>
        Hi, I'm <strong>Dian Hanifudin Subhi</strong> — a lecturer, cloud engineer, and backend
        developer based in <strong>Malang, Indonesia</strong>. I teach at
        <a href="https://polinema.ac.id" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Politeknik Negeri Malang
        (Polinema)</a> in the D4 Informatics Engineering program, build cloud infrastructure and
        backend services, and mentor developers in their early careers. Technology-agnostic,
        CLI-first.
      </p>

      <h2>What I do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Teaching</strong> — Lecturing D4 Informatics Engineering at Polinema, focusing on
          software engineering, cloud computing, and web development.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Research</strong> — Cloud Computing (SINTA-indexed, h-index 4, 30+ articles).
          Member of <a href="https://github.com/se-polinema" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@se-polinema</a>
          and <a href="https://github.com/laiba-dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@laiba-dev</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Engineering</strong> — Building and managing web applications, REST/gRPC services,
          and cloud infrastructure. Comfortable across the stack, happiest in the backend and DevOps.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Mentoring</strong> — Facilitator at
          <a href="https://dicoding.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dicoding Indonesia</a> for
          the DBS Foundation Coding Camp (Backend Developer learning path).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Tech I enjoy</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Languages:</strong> Go, Vue, Svelte, Lua, TypeScript, Python</li>
        <li><strong>Editor:</strong> Neovim (LazyVim · Catppuccin Mocha · Fira Code)</li>
        <li><strong>Environment:</strong> NixOS, Nix dotfiles (<a href="https://github.com/dhanifudin/dotnix" target="_blank" rel="noopener">dotnix</a>), tmux, zsh</li>
        <li><strong>Cloud / Infra:</strong> containers, Kubernetes, CI/CD, GitHub Actions, IaC</li>
        <li><strong>Web:</strong> Astro, Vue 3, Svelte — static-first, framework-agnostic</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>This site</h2>
      <p>
        Built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro 7</a> and
        styled to look like Neovim with the
        <a href="https://www.lazyvim.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LazyVim</a> distribution.
        The UI mimics Neo-tree, bufferline, lualine, which-key, and Telescope. Theme is
        <a href="https://github.com/catppuccin/catppuccin" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Catppuccin</a>
        (press <kbd>Space t</kbd> to toggle Latte ↔ Mocha).
      </p>
      <p>
        The site accepts contributions via GitHub issues using the
        <strong>OpenCode IssueOps</strong> workflow — the same workflow we use at
        <a href="https://github.com/se-polinema/se-polinema.github.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@se-polinema</a>.
        See <a href="https://github.com/dhanifudin/dhanifudin.github.io/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">CONTRIBUTING.md</a>
        for details.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/dhanifudin" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@dhanifudin</a></li>
        <li>Website: <a href="https://dhanifudin.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">dhanifudin.com</a></li>
        <li>LinkedIn: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/dhanifudin/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">linkedin.com/in/dhanifudin</a></li>
        <li>YouTube: <a href="https://youtube.com/c/dhanifudin" target="_blank" rel="noopener">youtube.com/c/dhanifudin</a></li>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:dhanifudin@gmail.com">dhanifudin@gmail.com</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </LineGutter>
</EditorLayout>
